# @servlyui/number-input Agent Notes

This package owns `ServlyNumberInput`, the atomic numeric input extracted from the portal `ServlyInput`.

## Ownership

- Keep this package focused on number-like values, units, presets, suggestions, and draggable numeric editing.
- Preserve support for integers and decimals. Use `numberMode` only to narrow raw number suffix behavior when a field explicitly needs integers.
- Treat Tailwind as the default preset design system. Keep custom `designSystem`, suffix option presets, keywords, and slot styling hooks working for consumers with their own systems.
- Do not export `ServlyInputText` or other generic input surfaces in v1.
- Do not import from `/Users/eddiesosera/Documents/Dev/Servly/noPrompt-portal` or use portal aliases like `@/`.
- Do not mutate `noPrompt-portal` unless the user explicitly asks for integration.

## Public API Rules

- Public props, refs, adapters, and events must live in `src/types.ts`.
- Public utilities must be intentionally exported from `src/index.ts` and `src/core.ts`.
- Keep `allowText` only as a deprecated migration alias for `allowCustomValue`.
- Keep `isTailwind` only as a deprecated alias. New behavior and docs should use `isDesignSystem` and `designSystem`.
- Keep animation libraries as consumer-side extensions. Use render props, adapters, and lifecycle callbacks instead of adding visual-effect dependencies to the package.
- Keep haptics as an opt-in extension entrypoint. Do not make the default component play audio unless explicitly requested.
- Core code must not statically import Ant Design, Lucide, react-icons, or draggable-number-input.
- Default styled behavior should come through `src/adapters/antd.tsx`.

## Tests

Add or update tests for:

- parsing, conversion, suffix detection, and formatting utilities;
- integer, decimal, and custom design-system preset behavior;
- controlled and uncontrolled rendering;
- typing, blur, suffix switching, suggestions, min/max, disabled/read-only, refs, and drag behavior;
- adapter precedence and the AntD adapter smoke path.

## Commands

```bash
npm run typecheck
npm run lint
npm test
npm run build
npm run pack:dry-run
```
